WhestBench is a benchmark for *white-box activation estimation*: given the weights of a small ReLU multi-layer perceptron (MLP) and a strict floating-point-operation (FLOP) budget, predict the average post-activation value of every neuron when the network is fed standard Gaussian inputs.
{% if split == "public" %}
**This is the Public Dataset Release for WhestBench 2026** — pre-baked MLPs paired with their ground-truth activation statistics, free to download and use while you develop your estimator. The actual evaluation is run against a separate, private holdout dataset under the same schema.
{%- elif split == "holdout" %}
**This is the private Holdout Dataset for WhestBench 2026** — consumed by the evaluator at grading time. It is not intended for participant download; the public release at `aicrowd/arc-whestbench-2026` is what you'll develop against.
{%- else %}
